revision.text:
{{New unreviewed article|source=ArticleWizard|date=April 2011}}

[[Image:Chidu suwajinja01 1920.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Suwa Jinja in [[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu]]]]

{{nihongo|'''Suwa Jinja'''|諏訪神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu]], [[Tottori Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. Known from the time of the [[Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions]], the shrine is celebrated for its [[Zelkova serrata|Zelkova]] and [[momiji]]. The [[Honden]] dates to 1832.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cms.sanin.jp/p/chizu/kankou/rekishi_miru/suwa/ |title=Suwa Jinja |publisher=[[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu Town]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> The Onbashira [[Matsuri|Festival]], held in the [[Tiger (zodiac)|Year of the Tiger]] and [[Rooster (zodiac)|Year of the Rooster]], sees pillars of [[Japanese cedar]] carried through the town.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cms.sanin.jp/p/chizu/kankou/rekishi_miru/hashira/ |title=Suwa Jinja Onbashira |publisher=[[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu Town]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>

==See also==
{{Commonscategory|Suwa-jinja, Chidzu, Tottori}}
* [[Suwa Shrine]]
* [[Suwa Taisha]]
* [[Matsuri]]

