{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}} {{Orphan|date=May 2011}} {{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|'''Suwa Jinja'''|諏訪神社}} | image = Chidu suwajinja01 1920.jpg | caption = Suwa Jinja in [[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu]] | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|35|16|16|N|134|13|53|E|source:kolossus-jawiki|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} {{nihongo|'''Suwa Jinja'''|諏訪神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu]], [[Tottori Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. Known from the time of the [[Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions]], the shrine is celebrated for its [[Zelkova serrata|Zelkova]] and [[momiji]]. The [[Honden]] dates to 1832.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cms.sanin.jp/p/chizu/kankou/rekishi_miru/suwa/ |title=Suwa Jinja |publisher=[[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu Town]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> The Onbashira [[Matsuri|Festival]], held in the [[Tiger (zodiac)|Year of the Tiger]] and [[Rooster (zodiac)|Year of the Rooster]], sees pillars of [[Japanese cedar]] carried through the town.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cms.sanin.jp/p/chizu/kankou/rekishi_miru/hashira/ |title=Suwa Jinja Onbashira |publisher=[[Chizu, Tottori|Chizu Town]] |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>
